get.description: Returns a list of all event ticket classes for a given issuer ID.

parameters.description: The ID of the issuer authorized to list classes.
parameters.name: issuerId

parameters.description: Identifies the max number of results returned by a list. All results are returned if `maxResults` isn't defined.
parameters.name: maxResults

parameters.description: Used to get the next set of results if `maxResults` is specified, but more than `maxResults` classes are available in a list. For example, if you have a list of 200 classes and you call list with `maxResults` set to 20, list will return the first 20 classes and a token. Call list again with `maxResults` set to 20 and the token to get the next 20 classes.
parameters.name: token

date.description: An ISO 8601 extended format date/time. Offset may or may not be required (refer to the parent field's documentation). Time may be specified up to nanosecond precision. Omitting the offset makes this a local date/time, representing several instants in time around the world. The date/time will always be in the user's current time zone. For example, a time of `2018-06-19T18:30:00` will be 18:30:00 for a user in New York and also 18:30:00 for a user in Los Angeles. This is useful when the same local date/time should apply to many physical locations across several time zones.

ticketLegs.description: Each ticket may contain one or more legs. Each leg contains departure and arrival information along with boarding and seating information. If only one leg is to be specified then use the `ticketLeg` field instead. Both `ticketLeg` and `ticketLegs` may not be set.

ticketNumber.description: The number of the ticket. This is a unique identifier for the ticket in the transit operator's system.

ticketRestrictions.description: Information about what kind of restrictions there are on using this ticket. For example, which days of the week it must be used, or which routes are allowed to be taken.

ticketStatus.description: The status of the ticket. For states which affect display, use the `state` field instead.

tripId.description: This id is used to group tickets together if the user has saved multiple tickets for the same trip.

tripType.description: Required. The type of trip this transit object represents. Used to determine the pass title and/or which symbol to use between the origin and destination.

validTimeInterval.description: The time period this object will be `active` and object can be used. An object's state will be changed to `expired` when this time period has passed.

resources.description: Resources corresponding to the list request.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string `"walletobjects#translatedString"`.

language.description: Represents the BCP 47 language tag. Example values are "en-US", "en-GB", "de", or "de-AT".

UpcomingNotification.description: Indicates that the issuer would like GooglePay send an upcoming card validity notification 1 day before card becomes valid/usable.

enableNotification.description: Indicates if the object needs to have upcoming notification enabled.

UploadPrivateDataRequest.description: Request for sending user private Text or URI by the Issuer.

issuerId.description: The ID of the issuer sending the data.

text.description: Private text data of the user.

UploadPrivateDataResponse.description: Response for uploading user private data (text or URIs)

privateContentId.description: A 64-bit content id for the private data that was uploaded by the Issuer.

UploadPrivateImageRequest.description: Request to upload user's private images by Issuers to be used in passes.

blob.description: A reference to the image payload that was uploaded by Scotty.

mediaRequestInfo.description: Extra information about the uploaded media.

UploadPrivateImageResponse.description: Response for uploading the private image

privateContentId.description: A 64-bit content id for the image that was uploaded by the Issuer.

description.description: The URI's title appearing in the app as text. Recommended maximum is 20 characters to ensure full string is displayed on smaller screens. Note that in some contexts this text is not used, such as when `description` is part of an image.

id.description: The ID associated with a uri. This field is here to enable ease of management of uris.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string `"walletobjects#uri"`.

localizedDescription.description: Translated strings for the description. Recommended maximum is 20 characters to ensure full string is displayed on smaller screens.

uri.description: The location of a web page, image, or other resource. URIs in the `LinksModuleData` module can have different prefixes indicating the type of URI (a link to a web page, a link to a map, a telephone number, or an email address). URIs must have a scheme.
